1. download
sudo apt-get install apache2

2.apache address:
Apache keeps its main configuration files within the "/etc/apache2" folder:
cd /etc/apache2

3.apache config
gksu gedit /etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf

add to 000-default.conf:

<VirtualHost *:80>
	ServerAdmin webmaster@localhost
	DocumentRoot  /home/matrix/workspace/www
    <Directory />
                 Options Indexes FollowSymLinks
		 AllowOverride None
		 Require all granted
    </Directory>
    <Directory /home/matrix/workspace/www/>
                Options Indexes FollowSymLinks MultiViews
                AllowOverride None
                Order allow,deny
                allow from all
    </Directory>


4.
sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 start   #start apache
sudo /etc/init.d/apache2 stop   #stop apache
sudo service apache2 restart    #restart apache

5. useful command

(1) check version:

apache2 -v    

(2)

